---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="AI Transparency" description="How I use AI tools on this website.">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">AI Transparency</h1>

    <div class="prose mt-10">
      <h2>Writing</h2>
      <p>
        Every post on this site is written by me. The ideas, opinions, and arguments are my own. I use language models for proofreading, testing phrasing, and sometimes as a sparring partner — but the responsibility for everything published here is mine.
      </p>

      <h2>Code</h2>
      <p>
        This website was built with AI coding assistants — from scaffolding and components to the deployment script. Code examples in blog posts are reviewed before publishing.
      </p>

      <h2>Why this page exists</h2>
      <p>
        I work professionally at the intersection of AI and corporate responsibility. Being transparent about my own use of AI tools is part of that. Not as a disclaimer, but as a stance: if something on this site is wrong, that's on me — not on a model.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
